article.headline: Grambling 80, Texas Southern 68
article.story: HOUSTON (AP) -- Andre Ratliff scored 24 points, including six 3-pointers, to help lead Grambling State to an 80-68 win over Texas Southern on Saturday night. Ratliff, one of three Tigers players to score in the double digits, also had a team-high seven assists. Brion Rush added 22 points and Jamar Lewis had 19 for Grambling (11-8, 9-3 Southwestern Athletic). Martez Stevens came off the bench to lead the team with 10 rebounds. The two teams were tied at the half but Texas Southern was outscored 43-31 in the second half on 48 percent shooting by Grambling. Texas Southern hit only 31 percent of their field goals in the second half. Christopher Moore had 16 points and 10 rebounds for his seventh double-double of the season for Texas Southern (5-18, 3-8). Sean Walker added 17 points, including three 3-pointers.
